    paragraphs:
      - A major basement rebuild involves more than replacing drywall and baseboards. Depending on the damage and the condition of the space, reconstruction may include framing, insulation, walls, flooring, ceilings, doors, trim, lighting, bathrooms, laundry areas, storage, cabinetry, painting, and complete finished living areas. Verawood Construction helps homeowners plan substantial basement reconstruction work with clear communication, professional project management, and careful attention to the finished result.
      - Before rebuilding begins, the basement should be dry, safe, and ready for construction, and the cause of the flooding should be understood. Sump pumps, backwater valves, drainage, sewer-backup risk, and other flood-prevention work may require licensed specialists. Once those concerns are addressed, Verawood can help plan the finished basement around your current needs—whether you want to restore the previous layout or create a better family room, office, guest space, gym, bathroom, playroom, laundry area, or storage space.
